Package curam.util.common.domain

Provides support for domain plug-ins that includes simple life-cycle management and supports a shared, thread-local plug-in context.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Domain A domain and its associated information.
DomainNames An interface defining constants for the names of the infrastructure domains.
DomainNames.Core Core domain names are supported by the infrastructure, but they are not necessarily root domains.
DomainNames.Root Root domains do not share a common ancestor domain and provide the base from which all other domains are derived directly or indirectly.
DomainOptions An interface to access the options that can be specified for a domain in the UML model.
DomainPlugIn A simple interface for all domain plug-ins.
Domains An interface to a collection of domains providing access to domains in the domain hierarchy by name and supporting the addition of new domains.
 

Class Summary
AbstractDomainPlugIn A base class for domain plug-ins that provides simple life-cycle management and supports a shared, thread-local plug-in context.
 

Exception Summary
DomainException Exception class for domain hierarchy problems.
 

Package curam.util.common.domain Description

Provides support for domain plug-ins that includes simple life-cycle management and supports a shared, thread-local plug-in context.
